 ('350', '384', 'en_us', 'Founder’s Day', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>On the first Sunday in October 1848, George Hendric Houghton gathered a band of twenty-four followers for a celebration of Holy Communion in the parlor of the home of the Rev. Dr. Lawson Carter, an elderly priest, on East 24th Street.  None of those first worshipers could have imagined that they had just attended the first service of the Church of the Transfiguration, later to be celebrated as ‘The Little Church Around the Corner’. The twenty-eight year-old priest who called this small congregation into being, however, had a clear vision in mind:  to establish a parish that would minister to the poor and needy of New York City. The first service in the new church was held on Sunday, March 28th, 1850.” <em>(excerpted from A Parish Guide to The Church of the Transfiguration by Zulette M. Catir)</em>    </p>\n<p>His motto was <em>Fides Opera</em>  (Faith and Works) \n</p>', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', 'Portrait of Dr. Houghton by Ralph L. Boyer', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2017-09-16 21:50:54', '2017-10-17 16:09:36', '2fe11b9b-78b6-48c0-990b-4a04a1af117a'),
 ('353', '387', 'en_us', 'Blessing of the Animals', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Bring your pets to our 11 AM mass on October 7 for a special St. Francis Day blessing. </p>', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2017-09-16 22:31:41', '2018-10-15 14:56:11', '74a69c4b-63d7-4f44-8cda-6fc8f3f5eaae'),
 ('354', '388', 'en_us', 'Open House New York', NULL, '', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Jesse Anders/On Point Images', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>The Church of the Transfiguration is excited to be part of the Open House New York weekend. Our church will be open for short concerts and tours on both Saturday October 13 and Sunday October 14. The schedule can be seen below. </p>\n<p><br /></p>\n<p>Saturday October 13 from 10:30 AM to 4:00 PM</p>\n<p> 11:00 AM .........Guided Tour: History, Art &amp; Architecture of The Little<br /> Church<br /> 11:30 AM ..........Concert: Wedding Favorites<br /> The Boys\' and Girls\' Choirs of The Church of the Transfiguration<br /> 12:00 PM ..........Guided Tour: History, Art &amp; Architecture of The Little<br /> Church<br /> 1:00 PM ............Guided Tour: History, Art &amp; Architecture of The Little<br /> Church 2:00 PM ............Concert showcasing the Arnold Schwartz Memorial Organ<br /> Dr. Claudia Dumschat, Organist/Choirmaster at The Little Church<br /> 3:00 PM ............Guided Tour: The Little Church from the Actor\'s Point of<br /> View<br /> Mart Hulswit, Executive Director Emeritus, Episcopal Actors\' Guild</p>\n<p><br /> Sunday, October 14 from 10:30 AM to 3:30 PM<br /> 11:00 AM ..........Solemn High Mass with Choir 1:00 PM ............Guided Tour: History, Art &amp; Architecture of The Little<br /> Church<br /> 2:00 PM ............\"A Celebration of Song\" Hits from Broadway and Beyond<br /> Members of the Episcopal Actors\' Guild<br /> 2:30 PM ............Guided Tour: History, Art &amp; Architecture of The Little<br /> Church</p>', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'http://onpointimages.com', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2017-09-16 22:37:49', '2018-10-15 15:04:25', 'a973c6bd-c811-423e-a2ad-f02ab265088f'),
