 ('950', '1083', 'en_us', 'Dr. Kyle Rader', '<p>Kyle Rader is a postulant for the priesthood in the Diocese of Chicago. Born and raised in Columbia, MO, he studied philosophy and religion at Truman State University in Kirksville, MO (graduated 2004), where he was a lay pastor of a small church. He moved to Chicago to study for ministry at the University of Chicago Divinity School (M.Div. 2007, Ph.D. 2016). Having been deeply formed in the Methodist tradition, he came to the Episcopal Church through Brent House, the campus chaplaincy at the University of Chicago (he still perks up a bit when the organist starts playing a Wesley hymn). He lives in Morningside Heights with his wife, Verena, who is a Ph.D. student at Columbia, and their sons Peter and Rasmus. He quit playing bassoon when he would have had to start making his own reeds, but loves singing, hiking, and dabbling in foreign languages (especially German).</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Seminarian', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2018-03-05 21:45:41', '2018-08-24 14:39:11', 'b1183b7f-f13c-4db5-84a7-49d4e133c74a'),
 ('951', '1084', 'en_us', 'Annual Choir Benefit', NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Please join us for our annual choir benefit \"An English Garden Party\" on April 29, 2018 from 6 to 9 pm!The evening will be held in the Grand Hall at 9 East 29th Street, and will include good food, wine, entertainment and prizes. This year, all proceeds will go to funding the choirs\' trip to St. Albans Cathedral in England. </p>', '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2018-03-06 15:11:05', '2018-03-06 15:11:05', 'd40a2d88-0284-4767-ae00-91dbceec7eab'),
 ('952', '1087', 'en_us', 'Choir Benefit', NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Save the date for our annual choir benefit on Sunday, April 29 from 6 to 8:30 pm in the Grand Hall of Transfiguration House, 9 East 29th Street. This year’s theme is “An English Garden Party,” an evening of good food, wine, entertainment, and a silent auction. All proceeds from the benefit will help pay for a unique opportunity this summer for the Boys and Girls Choirs, who have been invited to sing a week of Masses and Evensongs at the historic St. Albans Cathedral in England. This experience will greatly enhance their education, both musically and spiritually. Tickets may be purchased online at <a href=\"https://www.artful.ly/store/events/14764\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">https://www.artful.ly/store/events/14764</a><strong>. </strong>Click <a href=\"https://youtu.be/YG5aZJZxm0w\">here</a> to view a performance by the Boys at a recent Sunday Mass. </p>', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2018-03-06 15:19:20', '2018-06-07 13:23:23', '0dd5e6d3-acd4-4bc7-b74f-4335ec86781a'),
