 ('1112', '1258', 'en_us', 'Concert Series', NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>This program follows the evolution of the string quartet through Haydn’s life by featuring works from the composer’s most beloved and influential quartet collections. Quartet in F minor, Op. 20. No. 5 introduces a new dynamic to the quartet by showcasing four independent voices. Nicknamed “The Joke,” Quartet in E-flat Major, Op. 33, No. 2 belongs to the opus that the composer himself described as being “written in a completely new and special style.\"</p>\n<p> \n</p>', '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Cramer Quartet (Jessica Park)<br>A Haydn Retrospective<br>Tickets: $25, $15 for students and seniors</p>\r\n<p> \r\n</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2018-09-13 16:52:01', '2018-09-14 14:53:07', '0ce9218f-fd6b-44f0-8939-27df56978257');
