 ('1113', '1259', 'en_us', 'Concert Series', NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>String quartets in the 18th century were almost entirely performed in private, by and for connoisseurs. This capstone of Haydn\'s quartet development before his London sojourns exhibits a new accessibility and tunefulness as well as a remarkable balance of humor, pathos, and compositional mastery.</p>\n<p> \n</p>', '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>The New York Classical Quartet <br>Franz Joseph Haydn: Quartets from Op. 64<br>Tickets:$30, $15 for students<br></p>\r\n<p> \r\n</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2018-09-13 17:31:29', '2018-09-13 17:31:29', '903d27ca-099f-48a2-8d81-b89a9ba0ca48'),
 ('1114', '1260', 'en_us', 'Concert Series', NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Featuring the performance of Gabriel Faure’s sublime masterpiece Requiem.</p>\n<p> \n</p>', '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>The Transfiguration Camerata and Chamber Orchestra<br>An All Soul’s Day Mass Featuring Fauré’s Requiem <br>Tickets: Suggested Donation<br></p>\r\n<p> \r\n</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2018-09-13 17:41:50', '2018-09-13 18:44:39', '33442471-790b-4445-b75a-2cddd5ad0ba5'),
 ('1115', '1261', 'en_us', 'Concert Series', NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Renaissance and baroque music of France &amp; England, with guest Lucine Musaelian, viol and voice. The group focuses on the rich repertoire for two viols and harpsichord, while also indulging in daring and adventurous transcriptions of music originally composed for other instruments.</p>', '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Empire Viols<br>Channel Surfing<br>Tickets: $15 at the door</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2018-09-13 17:45:45', '2018-09-14 14:53:40', '0d7e456d-a26f-40b4-af8d-50bea2a10ad4'),
 ('1116', '1262', 'en_us', 'Concert Series', NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Vivaldi, a priest, music teacher and virtuoso violinist, composed this Gloria for the choir of the Ospedale della Pietà, an orphanage for girls, where he spent most of his career. This, his most famous choral piece, presents the traditional Gloria from the Latin Mass in twelve varied cantata-like sections.</p>', '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Christmas Candlelight Concert<br>Vivaldi’s Gloria<br>Voci from Monteverdi’s Vespers \r\n of 1610 plus traditional carols. <br>Tickets: $40, $25 for students and seniors</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2018-09-13 18:13:08', '2018-09-14 14:54:24', '53343878-1079-421e-9ff4-530aed09ac36'),
 ('1117', '1263', 'en_us', 'Concert Series', NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>This beloved opera was commissioned and first performed by the NBC Opera Theatre on December 24, 1951 in New York City at NBC studio 8H in Rockefeller Center, where it was broadcast live on television from that venue as the </p>', '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Amahl and the Night Visitors<br>Tickets: $25/$15 students and seniors</p>\r\n<p> \r\n</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2018-09-13 18:44:11', '2018-09-13 18:44:11', 'd8cbdd08-6dfe-4412-b74e-1beacda6f6e9'),
 ('1118', '1264', 'en_us', 'Concert Series', NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Violinist Gregor Kitzis and his Klang String Quartet have been wowing New York Composers Circle audiences for years at venues around Manhattan. And now NYCC is proud to bring their wonderful talents to Transfiguration! New works by NYCC members will be performed, including winners of the twelfth annual NYCC Composers\' Competition.</p>\n<p> \n</p>', '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>New York Composers Circle\r\n<br> Klang String Quartet<br>Tickets: $20 at the door, Free for students<br></p>\r\n<p> \r\n</p>\r\n<p> \r\n</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2018-09-13 19:01:26', '2018-09-13 19:01:26', '77df847a-cc6d-4236-93c1-b98d375e876a'),
 ('1119', '1265', 'en_us', 'Concert Series', NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Join us for this unique concert by Talisman Medieval, presented by David Yardley (countertenor, harp) and Christopher Preston Thompson (tenor, harp). Be transported to a different time and place by evocative works of the Middle Ages as well as original compositions and transcriptions from medieval manuscripts created by the performers. </p>', '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Friday, January 18, 7:30 P.M.<br>Talisman: David Yardley and Christopher Preston Thompson\r\n Winter Concert<br>Tickets: $15 at the door, concessions $10</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2018-09-14 14:39:27', '2018-09-14 14:54:08', 'aeed5be8-0aaa-4974-b4d1-8ec5cb7de1e2'),
 ('1120', '1266', 'en_us', 'Concert Series', NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Boccherini may not equal Haydn in abstract formal purity or ingenuity of motivic development, but he arguably surpasses Haydn in colorful textures, soloistic treatment of instruments, and extremes of mood, from exhausted languor to ecstatic exuberance, as shown in this selection of masterpieces deserving of wider hearing.</p>\n<p> \n</p>', '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>The New York Classical Quartet \r\n<br> Mozart: dedicated to Haydn \r\n<br> Luigi Boccherini<br>Tickets:$30, $15 for students<br></p>\r\n<p> \r\n</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2018-09-14 14:44:34', '2018-09-14 14:44:34', 'be78ae8a-fe8c-4cb3-9abd-239e4f941728'),
 ('1121', '1267', 'en_us', 'Concert Series', NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Transfiguration\'s Organist and Choirmaster Claudia Dumschat performs an eclectic range of new works by Frank Retzel, Raoul Pleskow, Chris Sahar, David Picton and more.</p>\n<p> \n</p>', '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>New York Composers Circle <br>Featuring New Organ Music Performed by Claudia Dumschat<br>Tickets:$20, Free for students<br></p>\r\n<p> \r\n</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2018-09-14 14:45:58', '2018-09-14 14:45:58', '0b786eac-9486-4439-a862-17b296cf5781'),
 ('1122', '1268', 'en_us', 'Concert Series', NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Treasured favorites from the varied repertoire of Empire Viols: Martha McGaughey, Carlene Stober, viols; Arthur Haas, harpsichord. </p>\n<p> \n</p>', '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Empire Viols <br>Spring Forward<br>Tickets: $15 at the door<br></p>\r\n<p> \r\n</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2018-09-14 14:47:19', '2018-09-14 14:47:19', '9ab338ca-f2e6-46e6-955a-1d0105bececc'),
 ('1123', '1269', 'en_us', 'Concert Series', NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>The Manhattan premiere of a group from Sunderman Conservatory at Gettysburg College. With fine musicianship, a new CD release, and dedication to new composers, this promises to be an excellent concert. New works by NYCC members will be performed. </p>\n<p> \n</p>', '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>New York Composers Circle: Wind Quintet<br>Tickets: $20 at the door, Free for students<br></p>\r\n<p> \r\n</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2018-09-14 14:48:13', '2018-09-14 14:48:13', '58690cd3-0dff-49e9-bd62-8ff50a99e262'),
 ('1124', '1270', 'en_us', 'Concert Series', NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Each opus of Haydn\'s quartets signals in turn a new approach of some kind. Op. 50, from 1787, while continuing these startling innovations and clear advances, is furthermore a synthesis and focusing of ideas and issues. These are works of a broad classical maturity, exhibiting virtuosity in composition and performance.</p>\n<p> \n</p>', '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>The New York Classical Quartet<br>Tickets: $30, $15 for students<br></p>\r\n<p> \r\n</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2018-09-14 14:49:20', '2018-09-14 14:49:27', 'e0a86f74-83b3-4583-a6a2-db04db0b72b4'),
 ('1125', '1271', 'en_us', 'Concert Series', NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Franz Schubert once wrote, “O Mozart, immortal Mozart, how many, oh how endlessly many such comforting perceptions of a brighter and better life hast thou brought to our souls!” By pairing both composers\' music together in concert, the Cramer Quartet pays homage to Schubert and his admiration of Mozart. </p>', '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>The Cramer Quartet\r\n<br> Schubertiade: Immortal Mozart<br>Tickets: $25, $15 for students and seniors<br></p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2018-09-14 14:50:24', '2018-09-14 14:50:37', '7b7f4c6c-5423-4bd6-9c42-9c779cc55ed6'),
 ('1126', '1272', 'en_us', 'Concert Series', NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Händel composed Saul with librettist Charles Jennens, with whom he also collaborated on the Messiah, and it was first performed in 1739. Tonight this oratorio is fully staged and performed as an opera. The dress is contemporary in order to clarify the characters\' relationships and stress their timelessness. The Transfiguration Choirs, Soloists, and Chamber Orchestra, Claudia Dumschat, conductor. </p>', '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Händel’s Saul<br>Tickets:$40, $25 for students and seniors<br></p>\r\n<p> \r\n</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2018-09-14 14:51:44', '2018-09-14 14:51:44', 'e1cea6fb-4272-4b8a-b8df-ca4fa416e43c'),
