 of his time, holding a mask and dressed in Greco-Roman costume.&nbsp; (Edwin Booth was the brother of the notorious John Wilkes Booth, President Lincoln\\u2019s assassin.) The window was given in his memory in 1898 by members of the Players Club, which he founded.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>And a few steps away, near the chancel on the northeast side of the nave, stands Richard Upjohn\\u2019s beautiful and intricate brass filigree pulpit.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>How fortunate we are to have works by all three of these masters under the roof of the \\u201cLittle Church\\u201d.&nbsp; I will give thanks when December 16<sup>th<\\/sup>&nbsp;rolls around.<\\/p>\"}}},\"25\":[\"93\"],\"26\":\"Mary Jane Gocher\",\"27\":\"Corey Schneider\"}}', '2017-08-30 15:21:52', '2017-08-30 15:21:52', '849cb71d-ed83-4707-8c3f-bda210182ebc'),
