 ('117', '234', '7', '1', 'en_us', '3', '', '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Our History\",\"slug\":\"our-history\",\"postDate\":1504211220,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"3\":\"\",\"13\":{\"236\":{\"type\":\"generalSection\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<h2>The Civil War<\\/h2><p><span class=\\\"s1\\\" <the=\\\"\\\" parish=\\\"\\\" had=\\\"\\\" only=\\\"\\\" been=\\\"\\\" established=\\\"\\\" for=\\\"\\\" a=\\\"\\\" few=\\\"\\\" years,=\\\"\\\" when=\\\"\\\" the=\\\"\\\" civil=\\\"\\\" war=\\\"\\\" broke=\\\"\\\" out.=\\\"\\\">span class=\\\"Apple-converted-space\\\"&gt;&nbsp; <\\/span>During this time, the church was a stop on the Underground Railroad, sheltering escaped slaves on their journey north.<span class=\\\"Apple-converted-space\\\">&nbsp; <\\/span>It was a place of refuge for African Americans during the New York Draft Riots of 1863 --three days of lawlessness, destruction, bloodshed, and lynchings.<\\/p>\\r\\n\"}}},\"11\":[\"235\"],\"12\":\"<p><span class=\\\"s1\\\">The Civil War<\\/span><\\/p><p><span class=\\\"s1\\\">The parish had only been established for a few years, when the Civil War broke out. &nbsp;During this time, the church was a stop on the Underground Railroad, sheltering escaped slaves on their journey north. &nbsp;It was a place of refuge for African Americans during the New York Draft Riots of 1863&mdash;three days of lawlessness, destruction, bloodshed, and lynchings.<\\/span><\\/p>\",\"27\":\"\"}}', '2017-09-04 20:45:14', '2017-09-04 20:45:14', 'd5110712-b60e-41f0-beee-cf09830639dd'),
 ('118', '234', '7', '1', 'en_us', '4', '', '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"A Brief History\",\"slug\":\"our-history\",\"postDate\":1504211220,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"3\":\"\",\"13\":{\"236\":{\"type\":\"generalSection\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<h2>The Civil War<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>span class=\\\"Apple-converted-space\\\"&gt;&nbsp; During this time, the church was a stop on the Underground Railroad, sheltering escaped slaves on their journey north.&nbsp; It was a place of refuge for African Americans during the New York Draft Riots of 1863 --three days of lawlessness, destruction, bloodshed, and lynchings.<\\/p>\"}}},\"11\":[\"235\"],\"12\":\"<p>Church of the Transfiguration parish was founded in 1848. &nbsp;The building itself dates from 1850; it was made a national landmark in 1973. &nbsp;The founder, the Rev. Dr. George Hendric Houghton wanted to build a church that would serve the needs of the poor and marginalized, and would welcome all regardless of race, class or background.<\\/p>\",\"27\":\"\"}}', '2017-09-04 20:47:46', '2017-09-04 20:47:46', '08a3212e-6f8b-4df0-aa41-d81e9749f0bd'),
