 ('129', '271', '7', '1', 'en_us', '1', '', '{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Outreach\",\"slug\":\"outreach\",\"postDate\":1504623411,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"3\":\"\",\"13\":\"\",\"11\":\"\",\"12\":\"<h2>Ecclesia Ministries<\\/h2><p>takes religious services to the homeless in Madison Square Park. It is a cooperative program supported by various churches and clergy in the NoMad (North of Madison Square Park) area. Transfiguration is one of those congregations; it is also the alternate location when inclement weather makes an outdoor service impractical. Last Christmas, our parishioners donated an abundance of warm gloves, scarves, gloves, hats, long underwear, and other items to people served by Ecclesia Ministries.<\\/p><p><\\/p>\",\"27\":\"\"}}', '2017-09-05 14:56:51', '2017-09-05 14:56:51', '783f958c-ff9c-4fa5-8f10-610bf397dcea'),
 ('130', '271', '7', '1', 'en_us', '2', '', '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Outreach\",\"slug\":\"outreach\",\"postDate\":1504623360,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"3\":\"\",\"13\":{\"new1\":{\"type\":\"generalSection\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<h2>Ecclesia Ministries<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>takes religious services to the homeless in Madison Square Park. It is a cooperative program supported by various churches and clergy in the NoMad (North of Madison Square Park) area. Transfiguration is one of those congregations; it is also the alternate location when inclement weather makes an outdoor service impractical. Last Christmas, our parishioners donated an abundance of warm gloves, scarves, gloves, hats, long underwear, and other items to people served by Ecclesia Ministries.<\\/p>\"}}},\"11\":\"\",\"12\":\"<h2><\\/h2>\",\"27\":\"\"}}', '2017-09-05 15:02:17', '2017-09-05 15:02:17', '67eeb4bb-9c4b-4a17-a2aa-b3d07893cf32'),
 ('131', '271', '7', '1', 'en_us', '3', '', '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Outreach\",\"slug\":\"outreach\",\"postDate\":1504623360,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"3\":\"\",\"13\":{\"272\":{\"type\":\"generalSection\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<p><a href=\\\"#\\\"><strong>Ecclesia Ministries<\\/strong><\\/a><strong><\\/strong> takes religious services to the homeless in Madison Square Park. It is a cooperative program supported by various churches and clergy in the NoMad (North of Madison Square Park) area. Transfiguration is one of those congregations; it is also the alternate location when inclement weather makes an outdoor service impractical. Last Christmas, our parishioners donated an abundance of warm gloves, scarves, gloves, hats, long underwear, and other items to people served by Ecclesia Ministries.<\\/p><p><strong><a href=\\\"#\\\">The Episcopal Actors Guild<\\/a>&nbsp;<\\/strong>was founded in 1923 by our third rector,&nbsp;the Rev. Dr. Randolph Ray to bridge the worlds of church and theater. Today,&nbsp;the Guild is a philanthropic organization that raises money and dispenses&nbsp;emergency funds to members of the acting profession facing severe financial&nbsp;hardship. It also has entertainment programs, educational, career development&nbsp;and social events for its members.<\\/p><p>Each November, the Guild holds a memorial service in the church dedicated to members of the profession who died in the previous year. In December, they present a Service of Lessons and Carols with outstanding music, often performed by Broadway veterans. Both events are open to the public.<\\/p><p><br><\\/p>\"}}},\"11\":\"\",\"12\":\"\",\"27\":\"\"}}', '2017-09-05 15:08:31', '2017-09-05 15:08:31', 'bd180617-caf0-4940-9d1b-b0d06ed681f8'),
 ('132', '271', '7', '1', 'en_us', '4', '', '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Outreach\",\"slug\":\"outreach\",\"postDate\":1504623360,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"3\":\"\",\"13\":{\"272\":{\"type\":\"generalSection\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<h2>Ecclesia Ministries<\\/h2><p><strong><a href=\\\"#\\\">Ecclesia Ministries<\\/a><\\/strong> takes religious services to the homeless in Madison Square Park. It is a cooperative program supported by various churches and clergy in the NoMad (North of Madison Square Park) area. Transfiguration is one of those congregations; it is also the alternate location when inclement weather makes an outdoor service impractical. Last Christmas, our parishioners donated an abundance of warm gloves, scarves, gloves, hats, long underwear, and other items to people served by Ecclesia Ministries.<\\/p><h2>The Episcopal Actors Guild<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p><strong><a href=\\\"#\\\">The Episcopal Actors Guild<\\/a>&nbsp;<\\/strong>was founded in 1923 by our third rector,&nbsp;the Rev. Dr. Randolph Ray to bridge the worlds of church and theater. Today,&nbsp;the Guild is a philanthropic organization that raises money and dispenses&nbsp;emergency funds to members of the acting profession facing severe financial&nbsp;hardship. It also has entertainment programs, educational, career development&nbsp;and social events for its members.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Each November, the Guild holds a memorial service in the church dedicated to members of the profession who died in the previous year. In December, they present a Service of Lessons and Carols with outstanding music, often performed by Broadway veterans. Both events are open to the public.<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><h3>Actor\\u2019s Pantry Food Bank<\\/h3><p><\\/p><p>Our parishioners support the Episcopal Actors Guild\\u2019s Actors Pantry (hyperlink)<br>program. Each Sunday, we collect non-perishable food. The Guild then fills<br>bags with the donated items and gives them to artists in need who have applied<br>to the Guild for help. No one leaves empty-handed.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><br><\\/p>\"}}},\"11\":\"\",\"12\":\"\",\"27\":\"\"}}', '2017-09-05 15:14:30', '2017-09-05 15:14:30', 'c336488a-c9e3-4719-836e-c687d77a87ac'),
 ('133', '271', '7', '1', 'en_us', '5', '', '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Outreach\",\"slug\":\"outreach\",\"postDate\":1504623360,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"3\":\"\",\"13\":{\"272\":{\"type\":\"generalSection\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<h2>Ecclesia Ministries<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p><strong><a href=\\\"#\\\">Ecclesia Ministries<\\/a><\\/strong> takes religious services to the homeless in Madison Square Park. It is a cooperative program supported by various churches and clergy in the NoMad (North of Madison Square Park) area. Transfiguration is one of those congregations; it is also the alternate location when inclement weather makes an outdoor service impractical. Last Christmas, our parishioners donated an abundance of warm gloves, scarves, gloves, hats, long underwear, and other items to people served by Ecclesia Ministries.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h2>The Episcopal Actors Guild<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p><strong><a href=\\\"#\\\">The Episcopal Actors Guild<\\/a>&nbsp;<\\/strong>was founded in 1923 by our third rector,&nbsp;the Rev. Dr. Randolph Ray to bridge the worlds of church and theater. Today,&nbsp;the Guild is a philanthropic organization that raises money and dispenses&nbsp;emergency funds to members of the acting profession facing severe financial&nbsp;hardship. It also has entertainment programs, educational, career development&nbsp;and social events for its members.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Each November, the Guild holds a memorial service in the church dedicated to members of the profession who died in the previous year. In December, they present a Service of Lessons and Carols with outstanding music, often performed by Broadway veterans. Both events are open to the public.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>Actor\\u2019s Pantry Food Bank<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>Our parishioners support the Episcopal Actors Guild\\u2019s Actors Pantry (hyperlink) program. Each Sunday, we collect non-perishable food. The Guild then fills bags with the donated items and gives them to artists in need who have applied to the Guild for help. No one leaves empty-handed.<\\/p>\"}}},\"11\":\"\",\"12\":\"\",\"27\":\"\"}}', '2017-09-06 16:30:07', '2017-09-06 16:30:07', 'ab407756-0944-4194-a6ee-36bbbaadce1a'),
 ('135', '239', '7', '1', 'en_us', '7', '', '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Parish Life\",\"slug\":\"parish-life\",\"postDate\":1504211760,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"3\":\"\",\"13\":{\"240\":{\"type\":\"generalSection\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<h2>Coffee, conversation, and culture<\\/h2><p>Sunday&nbsp;Coffee Hours also afford parishioners and newcomers opportunities to interact and to build relationships that often result in invitations to break bread or to take advantage of the many cultural events in New York. Fundraisers, like our Spring Music Gala, are also a great way to interact with fellow parishioners and to enjoy the talent and hospitality of our parish.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Sign up for our&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/lc-craft\\/grace\\/entries\\/about\\/new#\\\">weekly&nbsp;Friday&nbsp;blasts<\\/a>&nbsp;and check&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/lc-craft\\/grace\\/entries\\/about\\/new#\\\">our calendar<\\/a>&nbsp;for upcoming events and opportunities to participate in the robust Parish Life of Church of the Transfiguration.<\\/p>\"}}},\"11\":[\"238\"],\"12\":\"<p>Building community is an important part of Church of the Transfiguration both spiritually and socially. Many of our parishioners gather each week&nbsp;on Thursday&nbsp;to participate in worship and Bible Study, while others enjoy going to a local restaurant after&nbsp;Sunday&nbsp;mass to enjoy brunch and social fellowship.<\\/p>\",\"27\":\"\"}}', '2017-09-06 16:54:15', '2017-09-06 16:54:15', 'b9e0d79b-6e05-43c6-be40-d6d90d49b0a0'),
