 ('215', '115', '9', '1', 'en_us', '7', '', '{\"typeId\":\"9\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Do All Pets Go To Heaven?\",\"slug\":\"this-is-another-article\",\"postDate\":1504137600,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"28\":{\"116\":{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<p>Sem natoque nulla ligula ullamcorper facilisi semper conubia inceptos a risus aptent egestas dictumst vulputate at ultrices fermentum pretium hendrerit ad a. Suspendisse tristique consequat torquent ipsum hac cum a at ac at phasellus id fringilla dis risus auctor himenaeos parturient ac vestibulum dis faucibus litora. Ultrices et facilisi neque suscipit ad torquent convallis cras nisl condimentum a suspendisse felis vestibulum ridiculus suscipit nunc dapibus ac velit a.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<h2>Blessing of the Animals<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>Eleifend ut vivamus parturient hendrerit est parturient a nec elit a ante nec adipiscing condimentum velit montes metus eu sagittis enim. Turpis a diam ultricies arcu curabitur dignissim eleifend non aliquam interdum ad nulla tincidunt aenean aptent fringilla consectetur primis neque. Id scelerisque laoreet ad scelerisque ligula ut vestibulum praesent cras a habitant consectetur purus parturient. Eu laoreet nam in hac inceptos in hendrerit lobortis sociosqu cum elit aliquam condimentum ad a.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Vestibulum mi parturient auctor lectus suscipit curae litora lectus condimentum cubilia dui porttitor blandit ut. Faucibus penatibus a eros etiam pulvinar ultricies in a egestas vestibulum cum massa quisque interdum. Ullamcorper vestibulum parturient et mattis mi parturient sagittis praesent morbi netus condimentum fermentum ullamcorper ligula ante molestie hac phasellus facilisi class mattis blandit urna ridiculus ante magnis sociosqu a. Aliquet turpis ligula eros ad parturient parturient malesuada penatibus aliquet mi adipiscing ad pulvinar cubilia scelerisque laoreet penatibus vivamus a a scelerisque. Parturient ad massa cum nisi senectus massa taciti vestibulum accumsan magna in parturient nibh odio. A mi velit erat ullamcorper rutrum lacus vestibulum donec sit duis maecenas nam hendrerit gravida sed turpis enim scelerisque senectus laoreet quam lectus id adipiscing.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Adipiscing parturient ad condimentum at a ac lacus montes rhoncus arcu vel condimentum magnis venenatis praesent sem scelerisque dis eleifend urna gravida a ullamcorper a nisi ullamcorper sed lacus. Natoque vel nullam curabitur eu sem eu purus suspendisse et accumsan scelerisque adipiscing sit adipiscing suspendisse consectetur lacinia sociis commodo vestibulum natoque egestas. Ut faucibus fringilla habitasse elementum odio euismod adipiscing varius massa in parturient a gravida nostra sit.&nbsp;<br><\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Facilisi parturient tempus parturient interdum leo dis ullamcorper scelerisque odio vulputate feugiat suspendisse a eu varius hac diam neque phasellus tempor. Aenean maecenas a neque sed a a tortor vestibulum ad eu aptent consectetur nullam tortor. Vestibulum facilisis pharetra imperdiet nullam rutrum sem suspendisse a litora a id eu lacinia elit mus morbi a in in sociosqu ad in id torquent sodales.<\\/p>\"}}},\"25\":[\"206\"],\"26\":\"Fr. Patrick S. Cheng\",\"27\":\"\",\"70\":\"\"}}', '2017-09-30 09:02:30', '2017-09-30 09:02:30', 'deb551f9-00bf-4d68-9ffd-a83b46cd13e1'),
 ('216', '115', '9', '1', 'en_us', '8', '', '{\"typeId\":\"9\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Do All Pets Go To Heaven?\",\"slug\":\"this-is-another-article\",\"postDate\":1504137600,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"28\":{\"116\":{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<p>On October 8th, our parish will celebrate the Feast of Francis of Assisi with a blessing of animals after the 11:00 am mass. On that day, we will give thanks to God for our animal companions.<\\/p><p>We will also remember our beloved pets who are no longer with us. Many people wonder about what happens to our pets that have died. Is there such a thing as heaven for our pets? Do pets go to heaven?<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The traditional theological view is that animals lack immortal souls, and thus they do not go to heaven. According to this view, animals (as opposed to human beings) are not created in the image and likeness of God. As a result, they have only mortal souls and do not have eternal life.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>More recently, however, some theologians have suggested that animals might in fact share in God\\u2019s eternal life. They have pointed to biblical passages that describe the redemption of all creation \\u2013 human and non-human \\u2013 at the end of time. See, for example, Isaiah 11:6-9 (the wolf<br>will live with the lamb) and Ephesians 1:8-10 (all things in heaven and on earth will be gathered up in Christ).<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Similarly, in 2012, the governing body of the Episcopal Church authorized liturgical materials to be used at a service for the loss of a beloved animal. During the service, the officiant asks God to \\u201cgive us faith to commit this beloved creature of your own making to your care, for you live<br>and reign for ever and ever.\\u201d See General Convention Resolution 2012-A054.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>(Link to: https:\\/\\/www.episcopalarchives.org\\/cgi-bin\\/acts\\/acts_resolution.pl?resolution=2012- A054&gt)<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The words of this liturgy give me the hope that, one day, we will be reunited with our animal companions under the eternal care of God. Although we cannot have absolute certainty about this, we can hope that God\\u2019s love for all creation is so strong that it will overcome the pain of<br>separation and death.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>In my own view, heaven would not be, as the catechism in the Book of Common Prayer puts it,<br>\\u201ceternal life in our enjoyment of God\\u201d without the presence of our beloved animal companions.<br>See BCP 862. And so, I fervently hope that pets do in fact go to heaven.<\\/p>\"}}},\"25\":[\"206\"],\"26\":\"Fr. Patrick S. Cheng\",\"27\":\"\",\"70\":\"\"}}', '2017-09-30 09:05:58', '2017-09-30 09:05:58', '370eacac-93d3-4574-9c60-4a3d3b228628'),
