w depicting Edwin Booth, the leading Shakespearean actor of his time, holding a mask and dressed in Greco-Roman costume.&nbsp; (Edwin Booth was the brother of the notorious John Wilkes Booth, President Lincoln\\u2019s assassin.) The window was given in his memory in 1898 by members of the Players Club, which he founded.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>And a few steps away, near the chancel on the northeast side of the nave, stands Richard Upjohn\\u2019s beautiful and intricate brass filigree pulpit.<br><\\/p>\"}},\"122\":{\"type\":\"figure\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"216\"],\"altAttribute\":\"Richard Upjohn\\u2019s beautiful and intricate brass filigree pulpit\",\"caption\":\"<p>Richard Upjohn\\u2019s beautiful and intricate brass filigree pulpit<\\/p>\",\"credit\":\"Corey William Schneider, NY Adventure Club\",\"enlarge\":\"1\",\"orientation\":\"horizontal\"}},\"126\":{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<p>How fortunate we are to have works by all three of these masters under the roof of the \\u201cLittle Church\\u201d.&nbsp; I will give thanks when December 16<sup>th<\\/sup>&nbsp;rolls around.<\\/p>\"}},\"218\":{\"type\":\"footnote\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<p><em><em>Holy Women, Holy Men<\\/em>: Celebrating the Saints<\\/em> by Church Publishing Incorporated<br><br><em>Pictures featured on this blog are provided by&nbsp;Corey William Schneider, NY Adventure Club<\\/em><\\/p>\"}}},\"25\":[\"205\"],\"26\":\"Mary Jane Gocher\",\"27\":\"Corey William Schneider, NY Adventure Club\",\"70\":\"\"}}', '2017-10-06 14:23:52', '2017-10-06 14:23:52', '83a904c5-f2ac-4e16-8fad-998c5ba3d87d'),
 ('280', '671', '9', '654', 'en_us', '6', '', '{\"typeId\":\"9\",\"authorId\":\"654\",\"title\":\"\\u201cI\\u2019m Happy!\\u201d Says the Weeping Cherry Tree\",\"slug\":\"im-happy-says-the-weeping-cherry-tree\",\"postDate\":1507299000,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"28\":{\"672\":{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<p>Yesterday, a weeping cherry tree\\r\\nwas planted in Church of the Transfiguration\\u2019s garden and dedicated to the\\r\\nmemory of my brother, Mark Joseph.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><br><\\/p>\"}},\"673\":{\"type\":\"figure\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"679\"],\"altAttribute\":\"\",\"caption\":\"<p>Our new weeping cherry tree.&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"credit\":\"\",\"enlarge\":\"\",\"orientation\":\"vertical\"}},\"674\":{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<p>While I awaited the tree to be blessed, I reached to touch a leaf. The soft green blade filled me with Mark\\u2019s presence. Besides me was a group of friends to share in Father John David\\u2019s blessing of the new addition to the church\\u2019s garden. As we listened to Father\\u2019s prayer, a shaft of sunlight made it\\u2019s way through the surrounding buildings illuminating the young sapling. In the brilliance of God\\u2019s blessing for this autumn morning, I could see my brother\\u2019s smile.<\\/p>\"}},\"675\":{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<p>Mark was my youngest brother. Born with a learning disability, Mark&nbsp;met life struggles with remarkable courage even unto his death.&nbsp;Those who knew Mark, fell under his spell. He was funny,&nbsp;sometimes cunning, always affectionate, and never forgot anything.&nbsp;He could be introverted, but he could also be the commander-inchief&nbsp;of any gathering. His laughter was infectious. His love for&nbsp;others was sincere and true. It was rare for Mark not to say: \\u201cI\\u2019m&nbsp;happy!\\\"&nbsp;<\\/p>\"}},\"676\":