 ('322', '244', '10', '654', 'en_us', '14', '', '{\"typeId\":\"10\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Worship Schedule\",\"slug\":\"worship-schedule\",\"postDate\":1504260780,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"3\":\"\",\"13\":{\"245\":{\"type\":\"generalSection\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<p>At the center of our worship is emphasis on both Word and Table. Little Church clergy are considered <a href=\\\"#\\\">excellent preachers<\\/a>&nbsp;who connect lectionary readings with Biblical context and current challenges with a smattering of personal stories and humor. Transfiguration acolytes do an extraordinary job in ensuring the Eucharist is celebrated with majesty and dignity, and the authentic expertise of <a href=\\\"#\\\">our choirs<\\/a>&nbsp;draws worshippers closer to the love of Jesus Christ through some of the most beloved hymns of the Church.&nbsp;Below is the current worship schedule. Please consider joining us!<\\/p>\"}},\"658\":{\"type\":\"generalSection\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<h2>Preaching and Celebrant Schedule<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p><strong>October 29, 2017<\\/strong><br>Celebrant: &nbsp;Father van Dooren<br>Preacher: &nbsp;Father Cheng<br><\\/p><p><strong>November 2, 2017 (All Souls Day Mass)<\\/strong><br>Celebrant:&nbsp;Father van Dooren<br>Preacher:&nbsp;Bishop St. John<\\/p>\"}}},\"11\":[\"243\"],\"12\":\"<p>The cornerstone of Transfiguration\\u2019s spirituality is how we express and demonstrate God\\u2019s inclusive love through liturgy, music, and worship. As an Anglo-Catholic parish, Transfiguration honors traditional liturgy with a full complement of meaningful preaching and music.<\\/p>\",\"27\":\"\",\"70\":\"\"}}', '2017-10-23 14:29:07', '2017-10-23 14:29:07', 'bee53f5c-3177-4ea7-a7a2-bcaed485a710'),
 ('323', '244', '10', '654', 'en_us', '15', '', '{\"typeId\":\"10\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Worship Schedule\",\"slug\":\"worship-schedule\",\"postDate\":1504260780,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"3\":\"\",\"13\":{\"245\":{\"type\":\"generalSection\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<p>At the center of our worship is emphasis on both Word and Table. Little Church clergy are considered <a href=\\\"#\\\">excellent preachers<\\/a>&nbsp;who connect lectionary readings with Biblical context and current challenges with a smattering of personal stories and humor. Transfiguration acolytes do an extraordinary job in ensuring the Eucharist is celebrated with majesty and dignity, and the authentic expertise of <a href=\\\"#\\\">our choirs<\\/a>&nbsp;draws worshippers closer to the love of Jesus Christ through some of the most beloved hymns of the Church.&nbsp;Below is the current worship schedule. Please consider joining us!<\\/p>\"}},\"658\":{\"type\":\"generalSection\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<h2>Preaching and Celebrant Schedule<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p><strong>October 29, 2017<\\/strong><br>Celebrant: &nbsp;Father van Dooren<br>Preacher: &nbsp;Father Cheng<br><\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>November 2, 2017 (All Souls Day Mass)<\\/strong><br>Celebrant:&nbsp;Father van Dooren<br>Preacher:&nbsp;Bishop St. John<\\/p><p><strong>November 5 (All Saints Day)<\\/strong><br>Celebrant:&nbsp;Father Cheng<br>Preacher:&nbsp;Father van Dooren<\\/p>\"}}},\"11\":[\"243\"],\"12\":\"<p>The cornerstone of Transfiguration\\u2019s spirituality is how we express and demonstrate God\\u2019s inclusive love through liturgy, music, and worship. As an Anglo-Catholic parish, Transfiguration honors traditional liturgy with a full complement of meaningful preaching and music.<\\/p>\",\"27\":\"\",\"70\":\"\"}}', '2017-10-23 14:29:43', '2017-10-23 14:29:43', 'ef0f72b7-9479-48ae-9f59-8cd1c50c3e88'),
 ('324', '375', '10', '654', 'en_us', '3', '', '{\"typeId\":\"10\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Adult Education\",\"slug\":\"adult-education\",\"postDate\":1505579100,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"3\":\"\",\"13\":{\"376\":{\"type\":\"generalSection\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<h2>The Bible and Sexuality<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>Adult Christian education classes at Transfiguration will be finishing up&nbsp;a five-week series on the Bible and sexuality. Come explore what the Hebrew Bible, Apocrypha, and New Testament have to say to us today about topics such as marriage, sexual ethics, and LGBT issues.<\\/p>\"}}},\"11\":[\"374\"],\"12\":\"<p>Our Adult Education forums cover a wide variety of spiritual topics both within the Church and elsewhere. The series hosts a number of guest speakers and facilitators and promises an hour of entertaining and informational learning and discussion.<br><\\/p>\",\"27\":\"\",\"70\":\"\"}}', '2017-10-23 16:02:31', '2017-10-23 16:02:31', 'c1921ab3-2280-4ad2-9ea7-f3109b0a9318'),
 ('325', '826', '9', '654', 'en_us', '17', '', '{\"typeId\":\"9\",\"authorId\":\"654\",\"title\":\"Why Pledge?\",\"slug\":\"why-pledge\",\"postDate\":1508425440,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"28\":{\"827\":{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<p>Pledging changes everything! When I first pledged a tithe to a parish, my life was formed by it. It had to be! Jesus talks, again and again, about the immensely intimate relationship between money and our \\u201ceverything else.\\u201d It isn\\u2019t magic or gimmick - it\\u2019s simply one of the central spiritual principles of our Lord\\u2019s teaching. When we connect money to our faith, priorities get rearranged. Why? Because money IS spiritual.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>We might compare the connection between money and spirit to our Lenten discipline of connecting food and  spirit! When we give up a particular food that we love for the 40 days of Lent, we never forget that it is Lent, do we? Indeed, our appetite reminds us hourly of our small sacrifice. Similarly, money and spirit are connected! \\u201cWhere your  treasure is, there will your heart be also\\u201d&nbsp;(Matthew 6:21).&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;Pledging is also an act of thanksgiving. \\u201cOffer to God a sacrifice of thanksgiving, and make good thy vows unto the Most High\\u201d. (Psalm 50:14) Through our offerings, we thank God for all of the blessings he has given us. The pledge offerings that are received at Transfiguration help us to offer vibrant <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/littlechurch.org\\/worship\\/liturgy#entry:355:url\\\"><strong>liturgy <\\/strong><\\/a>and <strong><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/littlechurch.org\\/worship\\/adult-education#entry:375:url\\\">Adult Education<\\/a> <\\/strong>classes, maintain our <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/littlechurch.org\\/virtual-tour\\/lich-gate#entry:254:url\\\"><strong>historic building<\\/strong><\\/a> and peaceful <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/littlechurch.org\\/blog\\/2017\\/the-garden#entry:221:url\\\"><strong>garden<\\/strong><\\/a>, grow our <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/littlechurch.org\\/music\\/music-at-transfiguration#entry:324:url\\\"><strong>music program<\\/strong><\\/a>, and continue our inspiring <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/littlechurch.org\\/about\\/a-brief-history#entry:234:url\\\"><strong>history<\\/strong> <\\/a>of work for those in need. All of these wonderful ministries would not be possible without the pledges of those in our parish!<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Through pledging, you will transform your life, and the lives around you.&nbsp;If Transfiguration is not your spiritual home, I hope that you consider supporting your own parish this stewardship season. If you are interested in becoming a member of the Little Church and supporting the work that we do, you can fill out this year\'s <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/littlechurch.org\\/images\\/Pledge-Card.png#asset:829:url\\\">pledge card<\\/a>&nbsp;and drop it in the offering plate at one of our <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/littlechurch.org\\/music\\/music-at-transfiguration#entry:324:url\\\"><strong>masses<\\/strong><\\/a>. You can also mail or email it back&nbsp;to the <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/littlechurch.org\\/visit#entry:532:url\\\"><strong>church office.&nbsp;<\\/strong><\\/a><\\/p>\"}}},\"25\":[\"825\"],\"26\":\"Father John David van Dooren\",\"27\":\"\",\"70\":\"\"}}', '2017-10-23 16:36:30', '2017-10-23 16:36:30', '1c90b740-da06-474c-bb68-79e73107ef95'),
 ('326', '826', '9', '654', 'en_us', '18', '', '{\"typeId\":\"9\",\"authorId\":\"654\",\"title\":\"Why Pledge?\",\"slug\":\"why-pledge\",\"postDate\":1508425440,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"28\":{\"827\":{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<p>Pledging changes everything! When I first pledged a tithe to a parish, my life was formed by it. It had to be! Jesus talks, again and again, about the immensely intimate relationship between money and our \\u201ceverything else.\\u201d It isn\\u2019t magic or gimmick - it\\u2019s simply one of the central spiritual principles of our Lord\\u2019s teaching. When we connect money to our faith, priorities get rearranged. Why? Because money IS spiritual.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>We might compare the connection between money and spirit to our Lenten discipline of connecting food and  spirit! When we give up a particular food that we love for the 40 days of Lent, we never forget that it is Lent, do we? Indeed, our appetite reminds us hourly of our small sacrifice. Similarly, money and spirit are connected! \\u201cWhere your  treasure is, there will your heart be also\\u201d&nbsp;(Matthew 6:21).&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;Pledging is also an act of thanksgiving. \\u201cOffer to God a sacrifice of thanksgiving, and make good thy vows unto the Most High\\u201d. (Psalm 50:14) Through our offerings, we thank God for all of the blessings he has given us. The pledge offerings that are received at Transfiguration help us to offer vibrant <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/littlechurch.org\\/worship\\/liturgy#entry:355:url\\\"><strong>liturgy <\\/strong><\\/a>and <strong><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/littlechurch.org\\/worship\\/adult-education#entry:375:url\\\">Adult Education<\\/a> <\\/strong>classes, maintain our <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/littlechurch.org\\/virtual-tour\\/lich-gate#entry:254:url\\\"><strong>historic building<\\/strong><\\/a> and peaceful <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/littlechurch.org\\/blog\\/2017\\