 ('331', '244', '10', '654', 'en_us', '16', '', '{\"typeId\":\"10\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Worship Schedule\",\"slug\":\"worship-schedule\",\"postDate\":1504260780,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"3\":\"\",\"13\":{\"245\":{\"type\":\"generalSection\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<p>At the center of our worship is emphasis on both Word and Table. Little Church clergy are considered <a href=\\\"#\\\">excellent preachers<\\/a>&nbsp;who connect lectionary readings with Biblical context and current challenges with a smattering of personal stories and humor. Transfiguration acolytes do an extraordinary job in ensuring the Eucharist is celebrated with majesty and dignity, and the authentic expertise of <a href=\\\"#\\\">our choirs<\\/a>&nbsp;draws worshippers closer to the love of Jesus Christ through some of the most beloved hymns of the Church.&nbsp;Below is the current worship schedule. Please consider joining us!<\\/p>\"}},\"658\":{\"type\":\"generalSection\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<h2>Preaching and Celebrant Schedule<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p><strong>October 29, 2017<\\/strong><br>Celebrant: &nbsp;Father van Dooren<br>Preacher: &nbsp;Father Cheng<br><\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>November 2, 2017, 7:00 P.M.&nbsp;(All Souls Day Mass)<\\/strong><br>Celebrant:&nbsp;Father van Dooren<br>Preacher:&nbsp;Bishop St. John<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>November 5 (All Saints Day)<\\/strong><br>Celebrant:&nbsp;Father Cheng<br>Preacher:&nbsp;Father van Dooren<\\/p>\"}}},\"11\":[\"243\"],\"12\":\"<p>The cornerstone of Transfiguration\\u2019s spirituality is how we express and demonstrate God\\u2019s inclusive love through liturgy, music, and worship. As an Anglo-Catholic parish, Transfiguration honors traditional liturgy with a full complement of meaningful preaching and music.<\\/p>\",\"27\":\"\",\"70\":\"\"}}', '2017-10-23 18:53:35', '2017-10-23 18:53:35', 'e64810cb-aecf-47b4-b34f-6cb76806a81c'),
