 ('456', '244', '10', '654', 'en_us', '42', '', '{\"typeId\":\"10\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Worship Schedule\",\"slug\":\"worship-schedule\",\"postDate\":1504260780,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"3\":\"\",\"13\":{\"245\":{\"type\":\"generalSection\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<p>At the center of our worship is emphasis on both Word and Table. Little Church clergy are considered <a href=\\\"#\\\">excellent preachers<\\/a>&nbsp;who connect lectionary readings with Biblical context and current challenges with a smattering of personal stories and humor. Transfiguration acolytes do an extraordinary job in ensuring the Eucharist is celebrated with majesty and dignity, and the authentic expertise of <a href=\\\"#\\\">our choirs<\\/a>&nbsp;draws worshippers closer to the love of Jesus Christ through some of the most beloved hymns of the Church.&nbsp;Below is the current worship schedule. Please consider joining us!<\\/p>\"}},\"658\":{\"type\":\"generalSection\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<h2>Preaching and Celebrant Schedule<\\/h2><br><p><strong>January 28, 11:00 A.M. The Fourth Sunday after the Epiphany<\\/strong><br>Celebrant: Father van Dooren&nbsp;<br>Preacher:&nbsp; Mother Turner<\\/p><p><strong>February 4, 11:00 A.M. Candlemas<\\/strong><br><\\/p><p>Celebrant: Father van Dooren&nbsp;<br>Preacher:&nbsp; Kyle Rader<br><br><strong>February 11, 11:00 A.M. The Last Sunday after the Epiphany<\\/strong><br>Celebrant: Father van Dooren&nbsp;<br>Preacher:&nbsp; Father Cheng<\\/p><p><strong>February&nbsp;14, 8:00 A.M., 12:10 P.M., and 6:30 P.M. Ash&nbsp;Wednesday&nbsp;<\\/strong><br>Preacher:&nbsp;Father&nbsp;van&nbsp;Doore<\\/p><p><\\/p><p><\\/p>\"}}},\"11\":[\"243\"],\"12\":\"<p>The cornerstone of Transfiguration\\u2019s spirituality is how we express and demonstrate God\\u2019s inclusive love through liturgy, music, and worship. As an Anglo-Catholic parish in the Episcopal Church, Transfiguration honors traditional liturgy with a full complement of meaningful preaching and music.<\\/p>\",\"27\":\"\",\"70\":\"\"}}', '2018-01-22 20:51:56', '2018-01-22 20:51:56', '44c7831d-5e8a-4d15-991e-379743886091'),
 ('457', '244', '10', '654', 'en_us', '43', '', '{\"typeId\":\"10\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Worship Schedule\",\"slug\":\"worship-schedule\",\"postDate\":1504260780,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"3\":\"\",\"13\":{\"245\":{\"type\":\"generalSection\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<p>At the center of our worship is emphasis on both Word and Table. Little Church clergy are considered <a href=\\\"#\\\">excellent preachers<\\/a>&nbsp;who connect lectionary readings with Biblical context and current challenges with a smattering of personal stories and humor. Transfiguration acolytes do an extraordinary job in ensuring the Eucharist is celebrated with majesty and dignity, and the authentic expertise of <a href=\\\"#\\\">our choirs<\\/a>&nbsp;draws worshippers closer to the love of Jesus Christ through some of the most beloved hymns of the Church.&nbsp;Below is the current worship schedule. Please consider joining us!<\\/p>\"}},\"658\":{\"type\":\"generalSection\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<h2>Preaching and Celebrant Schedule<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p><strong>January 28, 11:00 A.M. The Fourth Sunday after the Epiphany<\\/strong><br>Celebrant: Father van Dooren&nbsp;<br>Preacher:&nbsp; Mother Turner<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>February 4, 11:00 A.M. Candlemas<\\/strong><br>Celebrant: Father van Dooren&nbsp;<br>Preacher:&nbsp; Kyle Rader<br><br><strong>February 11, 11:00 A.M. The Last Sunday after the Epiphany<\\/strong><br>Celebrant: Father van Dooren&nbsp;<br>Preacher:&nbsp; Father Cheng<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>February&nbsp;14, 8:00 A.M., 12:10 P.M., and 6:30 P.M. Ash&nbsp;Wednesday&nbsp;<\\/strong><br>Preacher:&nbsp;Father&nbsp;van&nbsp;Dooren<\\/p>\"}}},\"11\":[\"243\"],\"12\":\"<p>The cornerstone of Transfiguration\\u2019s spirituality is how we express and demonstrate God\\u2019s inclusive love through liturgy, music, and worship. As an Anglo-Catholic parish in the Episcopal Church, Transfiguration honors traditional liturgy with a full complement of meaningful preaching and music.<\\/p>\",\"27\":\"\",\"70\":\"\"}}', '2018-01-22 20:52:25', '2018-01-22 20:52:25', '598267e0-b380-4488-93e6-5be853dcc1fe'),
 ('458', '355', '10', '1', 'en_us', '12', '', '{\"typeId\":\"10\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Liturgy\",\"slug\":\"liturgy\",\"postDate\":1505416800,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"3\":\"\",\"13\":{\"563\":{\"type\":\"generalSection\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<p>Among those blessings are the gift of the Eucharist itself and the opportunity it provides for healing, both individual and collective. At Transfiguration the Eucharistic Liturgy&nbsp;(worship) offers a foundation for and pathway to deeper faith regardless of spiritual background or condition. In the words of the great Spiritual, \\u201clet us break bread together on our knees,\\u201d humbly asking God for forgiveness and for the strength and courage to do His will in our daily lives.<br><\\/p>\\r\\n<p><em>by Bill Glew<\\/em><\\/p>\"}}},\"11\":[\"251\"],\"12\":\"<p>The Gospels speak of troubled people seeking to touch the hem of Christ\\u2019s garment, that they might be healed. Christ\\u2019s garment is no more, but before He left this earth He gave us what our prayerbook calls \\u201ca foretaste of thy heavenly banquet\\u201d \\u2013 Holy Eucharist (or Communion or Mass), instituted at the Last Supper and celebrated every Sunday and weekday at the Church of The Transfiguration. \\u201cCelebrate\\u201d is the right word, because every Eucharist is a corporate giving of thanks to God for our many blessings.<\\/p>\",\"27\":\"\",\"70\":\"\"}}', '2018-01-24 10:45:55', '2018-01-24 10:45:55', '3b3b536f-a36d-481a-ba8e-52c38530085a'),
