 ('576', '244', '10', '654', 'en_us', '72', '', '{\"typeId\":\"10\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Worship Schedule\",\"slug\":\"worship-schedule\",\"postDate\":1504260780,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"3\":\"\",\"13\":{\"245\":{\"type\":\"generalSection\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<p>At the center of our worship is emphasis on both Word and Table. Little Church clergy are considered <a href=\\\"#\\\">excellent preachers<\\/a> who connect lectionary readings with Biblical context and current challenges with a smattering of personal stories and humor. Transfiguration acolytes do an extraordinary job in ensuring the Eucharist is celebrated with majesty and dignity, and the authentic expertise of <a href=\\\"#\\\">our choirs<\\/a> draws worshippers closer to the love of Jesus Christ through some of the most beloved hymns of the Church. Below is the current worship schedule. Please consider joining us!<\\/p>\"}},\"658\":{\"type\":\"generalSection\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<h2>Preaching and Celebrant Schedule<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p><br><\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong><strong>September 23<\\/strong><strong>:<\\/strong> The Eighteenth Sunday after Pentecost <\\/strong><br>\\r\\nCelebrant: Father Cheng<br>\\r\\nPreacher: Father Cheng<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><b>September 30: The Nineteenth&nbsp;Sunday after Pentecost<\\/b><br>Celebrant: Father van Dooren<br>Preacher: Seminarian Luke Zerra<\\/p><p><b>October 7: Foundation Day \\/&nbsp;Blessing of the Animals<\\/b>&nbsp;<br>\\r\\nCelebrant: Father Cheng<br>\\r\\nPreacher: Father van Dooren<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><br><\\/p>\\r\\n<p><br><\\/p>\"}}},\"11\":[\"1122\"],\"12\":\"<p>The cornerstone of Transfiguration\\u2019s spirituality is how we express and demonstrate God\\u2019s inclusive love through liturgy, music, and worship. As an Anglo-Catholic parish in the Episcopal Church, Transfiguration honors traditional liturgy with a full complement of meaningful preaching and music.<\\/p>\",\"27\":\"\",\"70\":\"\"}}', '2018-09-17 15:39:37', '2018-09-17 15:39:37', '6b710f0d-8e5c-4be8-a32d-98f36714ec5b'),
 ('577', '1075', '21', '654', 'en_us', '23', '', '{\"typeId\":\"21\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Adult Education\",\"slug\":\"adult-education\",\"postDate\":1519861140,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"3\":\"\",\"13\":{\"1076\":{\"type\":\"generalSection\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<p>Our next series, starting on September 30 will be \\\"Instructed Eucharist\\\" taught by Fr. Cheng.&nbsp;In this series, we will walk through the liturgy of the Holy Eucharist together.&nbsp; Participants will have an opportunity to observe the liturgical actions of the mass from the chancel and to ask Fr. Cheng questions about this liturgy.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;\\r\\n<\\/p>\"}}},\"75\":[],\"11\":[\"909\"],\"12\":\"<p>Our Adult Education forums cover a wide variety of spiritual topics both within the Church and elsewhere. The series hosts a number of guest speakers and facilitators and promises an hour of entertaining and informational learning and discussion. To download the full adult education year\'s brochure, click <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/littlechurch.org\\/images\\/Adult-Education.2018-2019.pdf#asset:1251:url\\\">here<\\/a>. <\\/p>\",\"72\":\"\",\"27\":\"\",\"70\":\"\"}}', '2018-09-24 13:59:03', '2018-09-24 13:59:03', '7be75f44-24d4-4d21-8cda-2f13b6463ae4'),
